
[1]quiescency

   QUIES'CENCY, n. [L. quiescens, quiesco. See quiet.]

   1. Rest; repose; state of a thing without motion.

   2. Rest of the mind; a state of the mind free from agitation or
   emotion.

   3. Silence; the having no sound; as of a letter.
